DOS-PORT (patch 0084, Phase 9 wave 17.5).

Wave 17.4 (patch 0082) tried partial flush via per-scanline diff +
SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects with a 2-4 rect list. Real-HW measured
**-7.1 fps regression** on title (PLAY1 = 18.5 fps with partial-flush
ON; PLAY2 = 25.6 fps with killswitch = wave-17.3 baseline). Each
dosmemput call carries a DPMI thunk + bank-switch setup cost (~3-5 ms)
that dwarfed the bytes-saved win on 2-4 rects. Per-rect flush =
32.6 ms; full-flush = 17.5 ms; per-rect was ~85% slower per flip.
See memory/wave_17_4_partial_flush_regression.md for the postmortem.

Wave 17.5 pivots: same prev-frame diff (wave 17.4's mechanism was
correct — memcmp produces real dirty bands), but COLLAPSE the 2-4
rect list to its bounding box and send ONE rect to
SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects. SDL/0033's per-rect path then issues
ONE dosmemput per flush — paying the setup cost once and pushing the
gap pixels too.

Wave 17.5 trade: bbox area is always >= rect-union area. The gap is
the cost we pay for one-call setup at PCI throughput. Threshold gate
raised from 50% (wave 17.4) to 75% (DIRTY_BBOX_THRESHOLD_PIXELS =
57,600 pixels) because below that the single-call setup wins over
full-flush even with the gap pixels.

Three changes to vendor/nxengine-evo/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp +
Renderer.h:

1. Renderer.h: new constant DIRTY_BBOX_THRESHOLD_PIXELS = 57600 (75%).
   New diagnostic accumulators
   (_prev_frame_diff_bbox_pct_x10_sum_block,
    _prev_frame_diff_bbox_threshold_exceeded_block).

2. Renderer::flip(): after the existing prev-frame diff loop, fold
   over _dirty_rects to compute bbox (min(x), max(x+w), min(y),
   max(y+h)). Threshold check: when diff is engaged, gate on
   bbox_pixels > 57600 (75%); when not engaged, preserve legacy
   50% gate on rect-union pixels. Partial flush dispatch passes
    to SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects — single rect, single
   dosmemput at SDL/0033's per-rect path. When bbox is empty (screen
   unchanged from prior flush), pass  for a no-op flush
   that still runs SDL palette / cursor plumbing.

3. Per-100-flip diagnostic line extended:

   The bbox_pct_x10 vs diff_dirty_pct_x10 gap shows how much overhead
   the one-call approach pays vs the per-rect approach (smaller gap
   = better trade).

DOSBox-X smoke (binary 87ea2e6a6759, 60s on title, default-ON):
- Intro (curmap=72): bbox_pct_x10 = 161-281 (16-28% of screen),
  threshold exceeded 0-9 / 100. Partial path 100% engaged.
- Title (curmap=1005): bbox_pct_x10 = 453-466 (45.3-46.6% of screen),
  threshold exceeded 0 / 100. Partial path 100% engaged.
- bbox-vs-dirty gap on title is only 2-4% (rects are tightly packed
  in a single parallax band — bbox is nearly optimal).

Real-HW prediction (per memory/perf_predictions_unreliable.md
honest variance: 5-30× off):

- Wave 17.4 PLAY1: 18.5 fps. Per-rect flush 32.6 ms.
- Wave 17.5 prediction: ONE dosmemput pushing ~46% of screen + setup
  cost ≈ 8 + 4 = 12 ms flush. Total flip 12 + 21 (other phases) =
  ~33 ms → ~30 fps title.
- Honest range: 0 fps gain (cost model still wrong) to +5 fps title
  (25.7 → 30.7).

Worst case: bbox always exceeds 75%, threshold trips every frame,
falls back to full flush. fps lands at ~24.5-25.0 (slight regression
from baseline because of the wasted diff CPU). DOSBox-X smoke shows
this WON'T happen on title (max bbox observed 46.6% < 75%).

Killswitch: SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF=0 still disables the
entire diff+bbox path → falls back to full flush (wave-17.3
equivalent). No new env var needed.

No SDL-side changes. SDL/0033 already handles single-rect dispatch
efficiently (in fact this patch makes that path the COMMON case).
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 103 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 src/graphics/Renderer.h   |  19 +++++++
 2 files changed, 108 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index 9bc152c..fa5216a 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -1956,16 +1956,61 @@ void Renderer::flip()
   // diagnostic block below).
   int dirty_pixels = 0;
   for (const SDL_Rect &r : _dirty_rects) dirty_pixels += r.w * r.h;
-  // DOS-PORT (patch 0082): accumulator for diff-engagement diagnostics.
+
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0084, Phase 9 wave 17.5): compute bounding box of
+  // the dirty rect list. Wave 17.4's per-rect dosmemput approach
+  // regressed -7.1 fps on real HW because each dosmemput carries a
+  // DPMI thunk + bank-switch setup cost (~3-5 ms / call) that dwarfed
+  // the bytes-saved win on 2-4 rects per flush. Wave 17.5 sends ONE
+  // bbox-rect to SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects → single dosmemput per
+  // flush via SDL/0033's per-rect path, paying the setup cost once
+  // and pushing the gap pixels too.
+  //
+  // For the non-diff path (_prev_diff_engaged==false), _dirty_rects
+  // already contains whatever the drawcall tracker produced — usually
+  // a screen-spanning bounding box from the wave-15 coalesce. Computing
+  // the bbox of that is a no-op (single rect → identical bbox).
+  SDL_Rect bbox = {0, 0, 0, 0};
+  int bbox_pixels = 0;
+  if (!_dirty_rects.empty())
+  {
+    int x1 = INT_MAX, y1 = INT_MAX, x2 = INT_MIN, y2 = INT_MIN;
+    for (const SDL_Rect &r : _dirty_rects)
+    {
+      if (r.x < x1) x1 = r.x;
+      if (r.y < y1) y1 = r.y;
+      if (r.x + r.w > x2) x2 = r.x + r.w;
+      if (r.y + r.h > y2) y2 = r.y + r.h;
+    }
+    bbox.x = x1;
+    bbox.y = y1;
+    bbox.w = x2 - x1;
+    bbox.h = y2 - y1;
+    bbox_pixels = bbox.w * bbox.h;
+  }
+
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0082 + 0084): diff-engagement + bbox diagnostics.
   if (_prev_diff_engaged)
   {
     const int denom = screenWidth * screenHeight;
     _prev_frame_diff_dirty_pct_x10_sum_block +=
         denom ? ((dirty_pixels * 1000) / denom) : 0;
+    _prev_frame_diff_bbox_pct_x10_sum_block +=
+        denom ? ((bbox_pixels * 1000) / denom) : 0;
   }
 
   const bool first_n_force = (_dirty_first_n_frames_remaining > 0);
-  const bool threshold_exceeded = (dirty_pixels > DIRTY_THRESHOLD_PIXELS);
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0084, Phase 9 wave 17.5): threshold check now uses
+  // bbox area against the 75% threshold (DIRTY_BBOX_THRESHOLD_PIXELS).
+  // The legacy DIRTY_THRESHOLD_PIXELS (50%) is preserved as a fallback
+  // for the non-diff path, where _dirty_rects content is the drawcall-
+  // coalesced screen-spanning rect that should still trip 50% threshold.
+  const bool threshold_exceeded =
+      _prev_diff_engaged
+          ? (bbox_pixels > DIRTY_BBOX_THRESHOLD_PIXELS)
+          : (dirty_pixels > DIRTY_THRESHOLD_PIXELS);
+  if (_prev_diff_engaged && threshold_exceeded)
+    ++_prev_frame_diff_bbox_threshold_exceeded_block;
   const bool can_use_dirty_path =
       _dirty_rect_enabled &&
       !_force_full_refresh &&
@@ -1990,8 +2035,23 @@ void Renderer::flip()
       SDL_FlushRenderer(_renderer);
       _renderer_queue_dirty = false;
     }
-    ok = SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects(_window, _dirty_rects.data(),
-                                      (int)_dirty_rects.size());
+    // DOS-PORT (patch 0084, Phase 9 wave 17.5): pass &bbox, 1 — single
+    // bbox rect → SDL/0033 per-rect path → ONE dosmemput per flush.
+    // For the non-diff path, _dirty_rects has at most one rect anyway
+    // (the drawcall-coalesced screen-spanning bbox); &bbox, 1 produces
+    // the same bytes-pushed as the prior &_dirty_rects.data(), N call
+    // would have. The win is in the diff-engaged case where N could
+    // have been 2-4 and we collapse to 1.
+    if (bbox.w > 0 && bbox.h > 0)
+    {
+      ok = SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects(_window, &bbox, 1);
+    }
+    else
+    {
+      // Empty diff (screen unchanged) — call with 0 rects. SDL3-DOS
+      // still runs palette / cursor plumbing without any dosmemput.
+      ok = SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects(_window, NULL, 0);
+    }
     ++_dr_dirty_path_taken_block;
   }
   else
@@ -2160,14 +2220,21 @@ void Renderer::flip()
                _dr_dirty_path_taken_block,
                _dr_full_flush_taken_block);
 
-      // DOS-PORT (patch 0082, Phase 9 wave 17.4): prev-frame diff
-      // attribution. diff_calls = how many flips engaged the diff path;
-      // rects_avg = avg rects produced per diff (lower = more uniform
-      // big bands, higher = more fragmented dirty regions); dirty_pct_x10
-      // = avg permille dirty area DURING diff-engaged flips. Compare to
-      // the dirty-rect-block dirty_pct_x10 above: the diff value should
-      // be MUCH lower on title screen (parallax + cursor only ~ 30-40%),
-      // proving the diff path is doing what it should.
+      // DOS-PORT (patch 0082 + 0084, Phase 9 wave 17.4 / 17.5): prev-
+      // frame diff attribution.
+      //   diff_calls = how many flips engaged the diff path
+      //   rects_avg = avg rects produced per diff (lower = more uniform
+      //               big bands, higher = more fragmented dirty regions)
+      //   dirty_pct_x10 = avg permille rect-union area during diff-
+      //                   engaged flips
+      //   bbox_pct_x10 = avg permille bbox area (≥ dirty_pct_x10)
+      //   bbox_thresh_exceeded = N/100 — how often bbox > 75% threshold
+      //                          tripped a fall-back to full flush
+      // Wave 17.5 trade: the bbox path sends bbox_pct_x10 / 1000 of the
+      // screen in ONE dosmemput vs the wave-17.4 per-rect approach which
+      // sent dirty_pct_x10 / 1000 across 2-4 dosmemputs. Win when the
+      // gap between dirty rects (bbox - rect-union) is smaller than the
+      // per-call setup cost × (N-1) extra calls.
       const int diff_calls = _prev_frame_diff_calls_block;
       const int diff_rects_avg = diff_calls
           ? (_prev_frame_diff_rects_sum_block / diff_calls)
@@ -2175,9 +2242,15 @@ void Renderer::flip()
       const int diff_dirty_pct_x10_avg = diff_calls
           ? (_prev_frame_diff_dirty_pct_x10_sum_block / diff_calls)
           : 0;
+      const int diff_bbox_pct_x10_avg = diff_calls
+          ? (_prev_frame_diff_bbox_pct_x10_sum_block / diff_calls)
+          : 0;
       LOG_INFO("prev-frame-diff block @flip={}: diff_calls={} "
-               "diff_rects_avg={} diff_dirty_pct_x10={}",
-               _flip_total, diff_calls, diff_rects_avg, diff_dirty_pct_x10_avg);
+               "diff_rects_avg={} diff_dirty_pct_x10={} "
+               "bbox_pct_x10={} bbox_thresh_exceeded={}",
+               _flip_total, diff_calls, diff_rects_avg, diff_dirty_pct_x10_avg,
+               diff_bbox_pct_x10_avg,
+               _prev_frame_diff_bbox_threshold_exceeded_block);
 
       _dr_total_calls_block = 0;
       _dr_dirty_rect_sum_block = 0;
@@ -2190,6 +2263,8 @@ void Renderer::flip()
       _prev_frame_diff_calls_block = 0;
       _prev_frame_diff_rects_sum_block = 0;
       _prev_frame_diff_dirty_pct_x10_sum_block = 0;
+      _prev_frame_diff_bbox_pct_x10_sum_block = 0;
+      _prev_frame_diff_bbox_threshold_exceeded_block = 0;
     }
 
     // Reset for next frame. _force_full_refresh stays whatever the
diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.h b/src/graphics/Renderer.h
index 485fadf..d8f742b 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.h
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.h
@@ -229,6 +229,17 @@ class Renderer
     // Threshold at flip(): if sum(rect.w*rect.h) > this many pixels we
     // fall back to full flush. ~50% of the 320×240 logical screen.
     static constexpr int DIRTY_THRESHOLD_PIXELS = 38400;
+    // DOS-PORT (patch 0084, Phase 9 wave 17.5): bbox-flush threshold.
+    // 75% of screen area (57,600 pixels at 320×240). Wave-17.4's
+    // per-rect dosmemput approach regressed -7.1 fps real HW because
+    // each dosmemput carries a DPMI thunk + bank-switch setup cost
+    // (~3-5 ms / call) that dwarfed the bytes-saved win on 2-4 rects.
+    // Wave 17.5 collapses the diff rect list to its BBOX → ONE
+    // dosmemput per flush at the cost of pushing pixels in the
+    // gaps between dirty rects. Threshold raised from 50% to 75%
+    // because bbox area is always ≥ rect-union area; below 75% the
+    // bytes-saved-vs-call-overhead trade still wins.
+    static constexpr int DIRTY_BBOX_THRESHOLD_PIXELS = 57600;
     // First-N-frames force-full count.
     static constexpr int DIRTY_FIRST_N_FRAMES = 3;
     // Diagnostic counters (per-100-flip block summary).
@@ -265,6 +276,14 @@ class Renderer
     int _prev_frame_diff_dirty_pct_x10_sum_block = 0;  // diag accumulator
     int _prev_frame_diff_rects_sum_block = 0;
     int _prev_frame_diff_calls_block = 0;
+    // DOS-PORT (patch 0084, Phase 9 wave 17.5): bbox-area accumulator
+    // for the per-100-flip diagnostic. Pairs with the rect-union
+    // dirty_pct above so the log can show both "bytes the diff said
+    // were dirty" (rect-union) and "bytes we actually pushed via
+    // bbox dosmemput" (bbox area). Bbox area is always ≥ rect-union;
+    // the gap is the cost we pay for one-call setup at PCI throughput.
+    int _prev_frame_diff_bbox_pct_x10_sum_block = 0;
+    int _prev_frame_diff_bbox_threshold_exceeded_block = 0;
 
     // DOS-PORT (patch 0071, Phase 9 wave 15): mark a destination rect as
     // dirty for the current frame. Clips to the 320×240 logical viewport,
